FBIS4-35838 "drnes108_p_94005" FBIS-NES-94-108 Daily Report 2 Jun 1994 SOUTH ASIA Afghanistan 1 Million Refugees Return From Iran 1 Million Refugees Return From Iran LD0206121694 Tehran IRNA in English 1130 GMT 2 Jun 94 LD0206121694 Tehran IRNA English BFN [Text] Zahedan, Sistan va Baluchistan Prov., IRNA -- One million Afghan refugees have so far returned to their country, the Interior Ministry's director general in charge of foreign national affairs 'Ali Husseini [name as received] said here Thursday. The return of the refugees was arranged by a tripartite commission comprising the governments of Iran and Afghanistan and the U.N. High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR). Preparations have been made for return home of some 300,000 more Afghan refugees this year, Husseini told IRNA. Husseini said that according to the policies of the Islamic Republic, those Afghan refugees who have received identification cards may stay in Iran as long as they wish. The commission has given those Afghans in Iran illegally until July 1 to leave the country, he said.
